      • getPower

        public double getPower()
        Description copied from interface: MotorCore
        Get a motor's power.

        Motor power is defined as a double between -1 and +1. -1 represents the fastest the motor can possibly spin - in the backwards direction. On the other hand, +1 represents the fastest the motor can possibly spin - in the forwards direction.

        Specified by:
        getPower in interface MotorCore
        Returns:
        a double, representing the motor's power.

      • set

        public void set​(double power)
        Description copied from interface: MotorComponent
        Set power to the motor.
        Specified by:
        set in interface MotorComponent
        Parameters:
        power - a double, with a range of +1 to -1 (positive one to negative one), that represents the amount of power the motor should receive. A power of 1 is 100% of the output in the positive direction. A power of -0.75 is 75% of the output in the negative direction.

      • get

        public double get()
        Description copied from interface: MotorComponent
        Get the motor's power.

        The returned percent power has a range of -1 to +1. Negative 1 represents the motor spinning as fast as it can, backwards. Positive 0.5 means the motor is spinning half as fast as it can in the forwards direction.

        Specified by:
        get in interface MotorComponent
        Returns:
        the motor's percent power.
